results.name: Decimal expansion of 2*Pi/3.
comment: Volume between a cylinder and the inscribed sphere of radius 1. - _Omar E. Pol_, Sep 25 2013

(2/3)*Pi is also the surface area of a sphere whose diameter equals the square root of 2/3. More generally, x*Pi is also the surface area of a sphere whose diameter equals the square root of x. - _Omar E. Pol_, Jun 18 2018
Volume of a hemisphere of radius 1. - _Omar E. Pol_, Aug 17 2019
